WE, THE PEOPLE OF INDIA, having solemnly resolved to constitute India into a 1[SOVEREIGN SOCIALIST SECULAR DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC] and to secure to all its citizens: 

<b>JUSTICE</b>, social, economic and political; 

<b>LIBERTY</b> of thought, expression, belief, faith and worship; 

<b>EQUALITY</b> of status and of opportunity; and to promote among them all 

<b>FRATERNITY</b> assuring the dignity of the individual and the 2 [unity and integrity of the Nation]; 

IN OUR CONSTITUENT ASSEMBLY this twentysixth day of November, 1949, do HEREBY ADOPT, ENACT AND GIVE TO OURSELVES THIS CONSTITUTION
